{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'm a writer and a journalist,"},{"time":3000,"text":"and I'm also an insanely curious person,"},{"time":6000,"text":"so in 22 years as a journalist,"},{"time":8000,"text":"I've learned how to do a lot of new things."},{"time":10000,"text":"And three years ago, one of the things I learned how to do"},{"time":13000,"text":"was to become invisible."},{"time":16000,"text":"I became one of the working homeless."},{"time":19000,"text":"I quit my job as a newspaper editor"},{"time":21000,"text":"after my father died in February of that same year,"},{"time":25000,"text":"and decided to travel."},{"time":28000,"text":"His death hit me pretty hard."},{"time":30000,"text":"And there were a lot of things that I wanted to feel and deal with while I was doing that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":34000,"text":"I've camped my whole life. And I decided"},{"time":36000,"text":"that living in a van for a year to do this"},{"time":38000,"text":"would be like one long camping trip."},{"time":40000,"text":"So I packed my cat, my Rottweiler"},{"time":43000,"text":"and my camping gear into a 1975 Chevy van,"},{"time":47000,"text":"and drove off into the sunset,"},{"time":49000,"text":"having fully failed to realize three critical things."},{"time":53000,"text":"One: that society equates"},{"time":55000,"text":"living in a permanent structure, even a shack,"},{"time":59000,"text":"with having value as a person."},{"time":61000,"text":"Two: I failed to realize how quickly"},{"time":64000,"text":"the negative perceptions of other people"},{"time":66000,"text":"can impact our reality, if we let it."},{"time":69000,"text":"Three: I failed to realize"},{"time":71000,"text":"that homelessness is an attitude,"},{"time":73000,"text":"not a lifestyle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":76000,"text":"At first, living in the van was great."},{"time":78000,"text":"I showered in campgrounds. I ate out regularly."},{"time":81000,"text":"And I had time to relax and to grieve."},{"time":85000,"text":"But then the anger and the depression about my father's death set in."},{"time":89000,"text":"My freelance job ended. And I had to get a full-time job"},{"time":92000,"text":"to pay the bills."},{"time":94000,"text":"What had been a really mild spring"},{"time":96000,"text":"turned into a miserably hot summer."},{"time":98000,"text":"And it became impossible to park anywhere --"},{"time":100000,"text":"(Laughs)"},{"time":101000,"text":"-- without being very obvious"},{"time":103000,"text":"that I had a cat and a dog with me, and it was really hot."},{"time":106000,"text":"The cat came and went through an open window in the van."},{"time":109000,"text":"The doggy went into doggy day care."},{"time":111000,"text":"And I sweated."},{"time":113000,"text":"Whenever I could, I used"},{"time":115000,"text":"employee showers in office buildings and truck stops."},{"time":119000,"text":"Or I washed up in public rest rooms."}]},{"cues":[{"time":123000,"text":"Nighttime temperatures in the van rarely dropped below 80 degrees Fahrenheit,"},{"time":126000,"text":"making it difficult or impossible to sleep."},{"time":129000,"text":"Food rotted in the heat."},{"time":132000,"text":"Ice in my ice chest melted within hours,"},{"time":135000,"text":"and it was pretty miserable."},{"time":143000,"text":"I couldn't afford to find an apartment,"},{"time":145000,"text":"or couldn't afford an apartment that would allow me"},{"time":147000,"text":"to have the Rottweiler and the cat."},{"time":149000,"text":"And I refused to give them up,"},{"time":151000,"text":"so I stayed in the van."},{"time":157000,"text":"And when the heat made me too sick"},{"time":159000,"text":"to walk the 50 feet to the public restroom"},{"time":162000,"text":"outside my van at night,"},{"time":164000,"text":"I used a bucket and a trash bag as a toilet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":167000,"text":"When winter weather set in, the temperatures dropped"},{"time":170000,"text":"below freezing. And they stayed there."},{"time":172000,"text":"And I faced a whole new set of challenges."},{"time":177000,"text":"I parked a different place every night"},{"time":180000,"text":"so I would avoid being noticed and hassled by the police."},{"time":183000,"text":"I didn't always succeed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":185000,"text":"But I felt out of control of my life."},{"time":192000,"text":"And I don't know when or how it happened,"},{"time":196000,"text":"but the speed at which I went"},{"time":198000,"text":"from being a talented writer and journalist"},{"time":201000,"text":"to being a homeless woman, living in a van,"},{"time":204000,"text":"took my breath away."},{"time":206000,"text":"I hadn't changed. My I.Q. hadn't dropped."},{"time":209000,"text":"My talent, my integrity, my values,"},{"time":215000,"text":"everything about me remained the same."},{"time":218000,"text":"But I had changed somehow."},{"time":220000,"text":"I spiraled deeper and deeper into a depression."}]},{"cues":[{"time":223000,"text":"And eventually someone referred me to a homeless health clinic."},{"time":226000,"text":"And I went. I hadn't bathed in three days."},{"time":229000,"text":"I was as smelly and as depressed as anyone in line."},{"time":233000,"text":"I just wasn't drunk or high."},{"time":236000,"text":"And when several of the homeless men realized that,"},{"time":239000,"text":"including a former university professor,"},{"time":241000,"text":"they said, \"You aren't homeless. Why are you really here?\""},{"time":245000,"text":"Other homeless people didn't see me as homeless,"},{"time":247000,"text":"but I did."},{"time":250000,"text":"Then the professor listened to my story and he said,"},{"time":254000,"text":"\"You have a job. You have hope."},{"time":257000,"text":"The real homeless don't have hope.\""},{"time":261000,"text":"A reaction to the medication the clinic gave me for my depression"},{"time":264000,"text":"left me suicidal. And I remember thinking,"},{"time":266000,"text":"\"If I killed myself, no one would notice.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":277000,"text":"A friend told me, shortly after that,"},{"time":282000,"text":"that she had heard that Tim Russert,"},{"time":284000,"text":"a nationally renowned journalist,"},{"time":286000,"text":"had been talking about me on national T.V."},{"time":288000,"text":"An essay I'd written about my father,"},{"time":290000,"text":"the year before he died, was in Tim's new book."},{"time":294000,"text":"And he was doing the talk show circuit. And he was talking about my writing."},{"time":297000,"text":"And when I realized that Tim Russert, former moderator of \"Meet the Press,\""},{"time":301000,"text":"was talking about my writing,"},{"time":303000,"text":"while I was living in a van in a Wal-Mart parking lot,"},{"time":305000,"text":"I started laughing."},{"time":307000,"text":"You should too."},{"time":309000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":310000,"text":"I started laughing"},{"time":312000,"text":"because it got to the point where,"},{"time":314000,"text":"was I a writer, or was I a homeless woman?"},{"time":317000,"text":"So I went in the bookstore. And I found Tim's book."},{"time":320000,"text":"And I stood there. And I reread my essay."},{"time":323000,"text":"And I cried."},{"time":325000,"text":"Because I was a writer."},{"time":328000,"text":"I was a writer."},{"time":330000,"text":"Shortly after that I moved back to Tennessee."},{"time":333000,"text":"I alternated between living in a van and couch surfing with friends."},{"time":336000,"text":"And I started writing again."},{"time":339000,"text":"By the summer of the following year I was a working journalist."},{"time":342000,"text":"I was winning awards. I was living in my own apartment."},{"time":345000,"text":"I was no longer homeless."},{"time":347000,"text":"And I was no longer invisible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":350000,"text":"Thousands of people work full and part-time jobs,"},{"time":353000,"text":"and live in their cars."},{"time":355000,"text":"But society continues to stigmatize and criminalize"},{"time":358000,"text":"living in your vehicle or on the streets."},{"time":361000,"text":"So the homeless, the working homeless, primarily remain invisible."},{"time":365000,"text":"But if you ever meet one,"},{"time":367000,"text":"engage them, encourage them, and offer them hope."},{"time":371000,"text":"The human spirit can overcome anything if it has hope."},{"time":376000,"text":"And I'm not here to be the poster girl for the homeless."},{"time":378000,"text":"I'm not here to encourage you to give money to the next panhandler you meet."},{"time":381000,"text":"But I am here to tell you that, based on my experience,"},{"time":384000,"text":"people are not where they live,"},{"time":387000,"text":"where they sleep,"},{"time":389000,"text":"or what their life situation is at any given time."},{"time":394000,"text":"Three years ago I was living in a van"},{"time":397000,"text":"in a Wal-Mart parking lot,"},{"time":399000,"text":"and today I'm speaking at TED."},{"time":402000,"text":"Hope always, always finds a way. Thank you."},{"time":407000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}